# Adding Applications

## Standard Flow (OCI Helm Chart)

```bash
./catalog-workflow.sh add-app --appname <name> --version <version> --ocirepo oci://<registry>/path/chart [--force]
```

Example:
```bash
./catalog-workflow.sh add-app --appname podinfo --version 6.9.4 --ocirepo oci://ghcr.io/stefanprodan/charts/podinfo
```

## After add-app

1. Verify OCI chart version exists (validation will fail if tag is invalid).
2. Update `metadata.yaml` if needed: **include category `dm-nkp-gitops-app-catalog`** (see catalog-category rule), plus description, supportLink, and other categories.
3. If chart needs CRDs or multi-step install, consider a multi-chart pattern (e.g. CRD chart + operator chart).

